 _D_i_s_o_n_a_n_c_e [Muž]35 [Kategorie]
27.04.2024 21:21:17
Proč je stonewalling škodlivý? Namátkou vybráno z anglického netu:

Partners who are stonewalled often feel demeaned or abused. They may even
begin to question their own self-worth.

the stonewalling person expresses that they do not value the other person's
feelings or perspective and want to make them feel isolated.

If done intentionally, stonewalling can be a form of gaslighting: Being
ignored or given one-word answers can make you doubt your (valid) concerns,
especially if your partner is also denying your feelings during an argument.

Aggressive stonewallers sometimes act like victims to protect themselves.

Passive aggressive partners are also called silent abusers and emotional
abusers. Stonewalling is a favored technique they employ to gain power and
control in a covert, underhanded way.

In the same way as gaslighting, stonewalling's a preventative tactic for
narcissists to escape their current situation. It's comparable to gaslighting
because they're manipulative and help shift the blame from them. It also makes
you question if you caused their behaviour towards you.
[Smajlík]
